# Project Rules for Background Agents

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all new code
- Follow ESLint configuration
- Use functional components for React
- Implement proper error handling with try-catch blocks

## File Structure
- Place new pages in `/src/app/[page-name]/`
- Keep components in `/src/components/`
- Use barrel exports (index.ts files) when appropriate

## NextJS App Router Conventions
- Use page.tsx for pages
- Use layout.tsx for layouts
- Use loading.tsx for loading states
- Use error.tsx for error boundaries

## Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Follow existing design patterns
- Use responsive design principles

## Testing Requirements
- Write tests for all new functions when applicable
- Use Jest and React Testing Library
- Focus on user behavior testing

## Documentation
- Add JSDoc comments for complex functions
- Update README.md for new features when significant
- Include usage examples for new components

## Git Commit Messages
- Use conventional commits (feat:, fix:, docs:, etc.)
- Keep messages concise but descriptive
- Reference task IDs when applicable

## Security
- Sanitize all user inputs
- Use parameterized queries for database operations
- Implement proper authentication checks
- Never commit sensitive data

## Background Agent Specific Instructions
- Always read the full task description before starting
- Create new branches for each task using the suggested branch name
- Test your implementation before marking as complete
- Update task status in the manifest when done
- Follow the existing project patterns and conventions 